Instruction:
Write C++ program to give specific Fibonacci number

Response A:
Here is a C++ program to give a specific Fibonacci number:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int fib(int n) {
    if (n <= 1) 
        return n;
    return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2); 
}

int main() {
    int n, fibNum;

    cout << "Enter which Fibonacci number you want: ";
    cin >> n;

    fibNum = fib(n);

    cout << "Fibonacci number " << n << " is " << fibNum << endl;

    return 0;
}
```

This program takes the n-th Fibonacci number as input from the user. It then calls a recursive fib() function to calculate the n-th Fibonacci number. This fib() function uses recursion and the fact that Fibonacci number is sum of previous two Fibonacci numbers if n > 1. Finally, it prints out the n-th Fibonacci number.

So it provides the desired functionality to output a specific Fibonacci number based on user input. The logic can be modified to store Fibonacci numbers in an array or vector as well for efficiency if needed.

